reviews.text: Great breakfast, freshly made, great team and environment.  Makes a world of a difference between hotel breakfast and breakfast at classified. The smoothie are great too.
If you ever find yourself in this part of the world, Hong Kong western section of the  island, try out some Sai Ying Pun western cuisine but with a local Chinese touch. Haay yung ha!
The steak here is a must-try! However, some of the dishes might not be quite suitable for Hong Kong people

Food was good but employees didn't know the restaurant well and told us false information.

One employee told us that the lunch sets were eligible for student discount but it turns out that it wasn't. We got charged full price.
Nice place for after hours drinks and bites. Cocktails and spirits are quite good for the price. Not very crowded so you can actually have a conversation.
